---

<MainLayout>
  <Header />
  <div class="page-body">
    <Sidebar />
    <main>
      <Section title="bio" id="bio">
        <p>
          David Pilo is the CEO and founder of Walcu, a leading ILM and CRM platform for 
          auto dealers. He holds bachelor's degrees in Mathematics and Computer Science 
          from Rollins College and a master's degree in Operations Research from Cornell 
          University.
        </p>
        <p>
          David began his career at Microsoft as a Program Manager on the Excel team, 
          where he helped make Business Intelligence tools accessible to a broad audience 
          and was part of the team that delivered Excel as a web application in Office 365.
        </p>
        <p>
          These combined experiences in technology, data, and digital transformation inspired 
          him to found Walcu, with the mission of delivering a world-class CRM built for the 
          automotive industry — combining the strength of global platforms with the precision 
          and fit of a vertical solution.
        </p>
      </Section>

      <Section title="last_updates" href="/posts" id="posts">
        <div class="articles-grid">
          {articles.map(article => (
            <ArticleCard {...article} />
          ))}
        </div>
      </Section>

      <Section title="projects" href="/projects" id="projects">
        {projects.map(project => (
          <ProjectCard {...project} />
        ))}
      </Section>
    </main>
  </div>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .page-body {
    display: flex;
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: 72rem;
  }

  main {
    border-left: 1px solid var(--sidebar-border);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    flex: 1;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    padding: 2rem 2.5rem;
  }

  main p {
    border-color: var(--section-line);
    border-style: solid;
    border-width: 0px 1px;
    color: var(--body-fg);
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono Variable', 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  .articles-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }
</style>
